  "conditionals": 61,
  "created": "2025-10-13",
  "description": "Sporulation in Bacillus subtilis is a last-resort developmental program triggered by nutrient starvation and mediated through a sophisticated multi-component phosphorelay system converging on the master regulator Spo0A. The system integrates multiple environmental signals (nutrient depletion, cell density, DNA damage) through five histidine kinases (KinA-E) that phosphorylate Spo0F, which transfers phosphate through Spo0B to Spo0A. Phosphorylated Spo0A~P activates sporulation genes and represses vegetative growth genes, committing the cell to the irreversible sporulation pathway. This represents one of biology's most complex developmental decisions.",
  "id": "bacillus_sporulation_initiation",
